    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03141.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ht" place="top">see notes Dec 2d 1888</note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Lapierre House</name>
                    <name type="place"><choice><abbr>Philad</abbr><expan>Philadelphia</expan></choice></name>
                    <date notBefore="1877-12-01" notAfter="1877-12-31">Friday</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Poet.</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I write you from NY asking you to be the chief figure in a box with <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="ej">Childs</unclear> <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="ej">Dayton</unclear> and self on the eve of the 24th <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="gt">inst</unclear> at the opening of my play at the Walnut St. Theatre. I have not heard from you. My dear friend are you not well enough to come? Longfellow was <choice><sic>ith</sic><corr>with</corr></choice> me at <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="ej">Boston</unclear>. Come and we will <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#gt">pet</unclear> you to death. We all want so much to see you.</p>
            
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours</salute>
                <signed>Joaquin Miller</signed>
            </closer>
            
